      • charsToNum

        static int charsToNum(CharStack stack,
                      int n)
        Given a stack of characters from a compressed proof and a starting value n, calculates a numerical value for the stack. If the stack is empty, n is returned. Otherwise, let N_k ... N_0 be the numbers on the stack, with N_0 at the top of the stack. Then the final value returned is n + 20 * (N_0 * 5^0 + ... + N_k * 5^k).
        Parameters:
        stack - a possibly empty stack of characters
        n - the starting integer value
        Returns:
        the numerical value of the stack plus the starting integer

      • decompress

        String[] decompress(String[] compressedProof)
             throws MMException
        Given a proof in compressed form, returns the proof in normal form. Compressed proofs are verified directly, so this method is never used. But in principle we could decompress them with this method and apply verifyNormal() to the results (see decompressTester()).
        Parameters:
        compressedProof - a string array containing the compressed proof
        Returns:
        a string array containing the proof in normal format
        Throws:
        MMException - if the compressed proof is invalidly structured

      • decompressTester

        boolean decompressTester()
                  throws MMException
        To test the decompress() method, rename verify() to verifyOLD() and this method to verify().
        Throws:
        MMException
